This article is a copy of an executive order issued by President Barack Obama on May 13, 2014. The executive order is titled "Blocking Property of Certain Persons Contributing to the Conflict in the Central African Republic." The order declares a national emergency due to the situation in and in relation to the Central African Republic, which includes a breakdown of law and order, sectarian tension, violence, and the use of child soldiers. The order blocks the property and interests in property of certain individuals and entities who are determined to be contributing to the conflict or engaging in activities that threaten the peace, security, or stability of the Central African Republic. The order also prohibits the making of donations to these individuals or entities and suspends the entry into the United States of aliens determined to meet the criteria outlined in the order. The Secretary of the Treasury is authorized to take necessary actions to carry out the order, and periodic reports on the national emergency are to be submitted to Congress.